            </div>
        </div>
        <i>
            “When Rory Gallagher passed away, his brother Donel was still rooting for him and looking after this

            affairs. He got about four statues of Rory erected in memory of him, and several streets named after

            him in Cork and Paris, as well as a festival every year in Ballyshannon in honour of him. Philip’s mother

            has done so much for him since he died. A statue in Dublin, a book about him, an annual show, Vibe for

            Philo, that’s been going for 30 years. I'm playing that as well in January. That got me thinking about my

            good friend Gary Moore. There are no streets named after Gary, no statues of Gary. The guy was an

            amazing international guitar player, he sold millions of albums, played with BB King and some of the

            greatest blues guitarists of all time. Yet there’s been no fuss made of his passing. I thought, what can I

            do? I can write a song about him. That’s my little offering, my tribute to Gary which will be on the new

            album, 'Exile'. That's why I'm so pleased to play this tribute gig for Gary to get him the statue he

            deserves.”
        </i><p> Eric Bell</p>
